inversion\" applied to real UVCS and LASCO data allowed\nalso to reconstruct the typical bimodal distribution of fast and slow wind at\nsolar minimum, and to derive a more complex picture around solar maximum. The\napplication of the technique shown here will be very important for the future\nanalyses of data acquired with multichannel WL and UV (Ly-alpha) coronagraphs,\nsuch as Metis on-board Solar Orbiter, LST on-board ASO-S, and any other future\nWL and UV Ly-alpha multi-channel coronagraph.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 14 Jul 2021 16:10:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-10-13"}
