e decay rate $\\Gamma(B\\to e^{+}e^{-}e \\nu_e)$ receives comparable\ncontributions from the region near $q^2\\sim 4m_e^2$ and from the resonance\nregion; (iii) One finds a strong enhancement of the decay rate $\\Gamma(B\\to\ne^+e^- \\mu \\nu_\\mu)\\sim m_\\mu^2/m_e^2$ which is dominated by the region\n$q^2\\sim 4m_e^2$ due to the terms $O(m_\\mu^2/q^4)$ in the differential\ndistribution.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 15 Jul 2021 11:11:26 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 22 Sep 2021 14:04:16 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 25 Nov 2021 10:07:33 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 12 Jan 2022 20:34:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-01-28"}
